node.text:
Sliding through the forests of Borsec in Romania with @ivnicoara 🤪

The new Sunkid Mountain Coaster with its 1,440 metres is one of the longest summer toboggan runs Romania has to offer.

The small town of Borsec with its 2,500 residents is about 50 kilometres to the west of Durau. A popular spa in the times of the Royal and Imperial Monarchy, the place is currently developing an upwards trend. Since this summer, its guests are able to enjoy a new Sunkid Mountain Coaster as well. At a total length of 1,440 metres, with 575 metres used for mountain transport and 865 metres for the downhill run, the Borsec Mountain Coaster is one of the longest summer toboggan runs Romania has to offer with a maximum speed of 40 km/h and inclinations of 15%.

Would you like to try this mountain coaster? Tag someone you would share this experience with! 🤯

📽 @ivnicoara #nature
📍 Mountain Coaster Borsec, Romania
🎶 Kaleo - Way Down We Go

node.text:
Summertime in Polignano a Mare 😍 Lama Monachile is a small public beach in Polignano a Mare, located near the historical center of the city.

This compact cove is also called Cala Porto and it's known for its clear water & pebble beach, flanked by dramatic, rugged cliffs.

📽 @terplanet #nature
📍Lama Monachile, Polignano a Mare, Italy
🎶 Con te partirò - Andrea Bocelli
